. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[524,544,1979,2005]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">E</emphasis>
. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="49.[189,334,267,293]" box="[189,334,267,293]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,267,293]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[189,506,314,375]" box="[234,325,314,340]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,325,314,340]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Female</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[189,506,314,375]" box="[189,506,348,375]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">BODY LENGTH. 4.6–5.0 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[189,1399,414,581]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
HEAD. Head slightly wider than long. Integument black, except part of mandibles dark reddish-brown. Face sparsely covered with long, greyish, erect hair (
<figureCitation box="[836,950,449,476]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="48.[189,232,1943,1969]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,562,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[189,1399,561,1894]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Fig. 25. Scrapter pygmaeus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860648/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 25A</figureCitation>
). Clypeus almost flat, with dispersed large, shallow punctation (i = 1–2 d); surface between punctures apically smooth or only superficially sculptured, shiny, basally more heavily sculptured and matt (
<figureCitation box="[924,1035,519,546]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="48.[189,232,1943,1969]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,562,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[189,1399,561,1894]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Fig. 25. Scrapter pygmaeus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860648/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 25B</figureCitation>
). Malar area medially narrow, almost linear. Antenna dorsally blackish-brown, ventrally yellowish-brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[189,1398,620,788]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
MESOSOMA. Integument black. Mesoscutal disc between punctures strongly reticulate, matt; disc sparsely (i = 2–3 d), finely and shallowly punctate (
<figureCitation box="[692,777,655,682]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="48.[189,232,1943,1969]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,562,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[189,1399,561,1894]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Fig. 25. Scrapter pygmaeus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860648/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
C–D). Metanotum about half as long as basal area of propodeum, apically with indistinct narrow carinate depression (
<figureCitation box="[964,1077,690,717]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="48.[189,232,1943,1969]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,562,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[189,1399,561,1894]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Fig. 25. Scrapter pygmaeus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860648/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 25D</figureCitation>
). Propodeum with shallow carination covering about half of the basal area (
<figureCitation box="[810,926,726,753]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="48.[189,232,1943,1969]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,562,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[189,1399,561,1894]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Fig. 25. Scrapter pygmaeus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860648/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 25D</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum, scutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum sparsely covered with short, greyish, erect hair (
<figureCitation box="[1128,1238,761,788]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="48.[189,232,1943,1969]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,562,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[189,1399,561,1894]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Fig. 25. Scrapter pygmaeus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860648/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 25A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[189,888,826,853]" box="[189,888,826,853]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">WINGS. Yellowish-brown; wing venation and stigma brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[189,1398,892,954]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">LEGS. Integument black to dark reddish-brown; fore tibia basally with small yellow spot. Vestiture greyish-white, scopa greyish-white, dorsally blackish-brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[189,1399,992,1195]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
METASOMA. Integument black, apical margins of terga sometimes narrowly translucent yellowish to dark reddish-brown (
<figureCitation box="[374,479,1028,1055]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="48.[189,232,1943,1969]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,562,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[189,1399,561,1894]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Fig. 25. Scrapter pygmaeus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860648/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 25E</figureCitation>
). Disc of T1 without hair; following terga with sparse and short but increasingly more and longer hair; T2 and T3 basally with a medially very narrow, laterally much broader band of very fine, short and erect, silverish hair; apical tergal hair bands missing on all terga (
<figureCitation box="[1276,1386,1098,1125]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="48.[189,232,1943,1969]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,562,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[189,1399,561,1894]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Fig. 25. Scrapter pygmaeus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860648/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 25E</figureCitation>
). Prepygidial and pygidial fimbriae yellowish-brown. Terga impunctate, superficially and ± densely sculptured, mostly shiny; T2–T4 with finely sculptured, broad apical tergal depression (
<figureCitation box="[1216,1322,1168,1195]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="48.[189,232,1943,1969]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,562,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@48.[189,1399,561,1894]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Fig. 25. Scrapter pygmaeus sp. nov., ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Head (SEM). C. Thorax (dorsal view). D. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). E. Metasoma (dorsal view). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860648/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 25E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[189,313,1234,1295]" box="[234,298,1234,1260]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,1234,1260]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[189,313,1234,1295]" box="[189,313,1269,1295]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
